/nextinsurance.wpengine.com/?p=31',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(32,2,'2016-07-31 14:15:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2016-07-31 14:15:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',4,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/?p=32',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(33,2,'2016-07-31 14:44:57','2016-07-31 14:44:57',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','33','','','2016-07-31 14:44:57','2016-07-31 14:44:57','',4,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/?p=33',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(34,2,'2016-07-31 14:53:00','2016-07-31 14:53:00','<img class=\"wp-image-37 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/iStock_27033536_SMALL.jpg\" alt=\"Successful couple of young athletes raising arms to golden summer sunset sky after training. Fitness man and woman with arms up celebrating sport goals after exercising in countryside field.\" width=\"847\" height=\"566\" />Personal trainer insurance is critical if you are a credentialed personal trainer. You can be sued – even if you have done nothing wrong. Personal trainers can be sued for injuries sustained during workouts, chronic pain experienced after fitness training, or even bodily damage that occurs during training through no fault of your own. Your best solution is to protect yourself with personal trainer  insurance.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What kind of Liability Insurance is best for you?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe coverage that is best for you depends on the details of your business. Many customers optimize their personal trainer insurance by choosing both professional liability insurance and general liability insurance policies. To assure that you get the best coverage for your business, see the examples below.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Professional Liability Insurance</strong>\r\n\r\nSometimes called errors and omissions insurance (E&amp;O insurance), is personal trainer insurance coverage for claims against businesses that provide professional and personal services – for businesses like yours. When is it important to have professional liability insurance for personal trainers? Examples include:\r\n\r\nClaims of Negligence:A personal trainer instructs an older client to perform a specific exercise that involves a lot of physical exertion. Following the exercise, the client feels dizzy and experiences chest pain and has to be rushed to the hospital. The client later claims that the trainer caused her heart attack and mental anguish. Having professional liability insurance (errors and omissions insurance) protects you if such a claim is made.\r\n\r\nLoss of personal information: By mistake, you misplace a file with  sensitive client information, including financial information. It was an accident of course, and the information is compromised.  If your client sues you, we will cover claims subject to your limit of insurance.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAlso known as malpractice insurance for personal trainers, professional liability protects personal trainers if they are sued for making a mistake. It’s important to note that you can be sued for malpractice whether you actually made a mistake or not, and such a lawsuit can arise months or years after the event allegedly took place.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLearn more about professional liability insurance or watch our professional liability insurance guide.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSometimes called commercial general liability (CGL) is personal trainer insurance that protects your business from another person or business\'s claims of bodily injury, associated medical costs and damage to property. Having this kind of coverage is beneficial in several instances:\r\n\r\nBodily injury: While waiting to begin a personal training session, a client accidentally trips over another customer’s gym bag and blames the trainer for not keeping the area clear. General liability insurance protects you against third-party claims for bodily injury and,  the extent you are liable up to your policy limits, and related medical costs.\r\n\r\nProperty damage: You’re visiting a client’s home and accidentally knock over a computer monitor, breaking it. Your general liability policy will cover the subsequent claim, up to your policy\'s limits of liability.','Personal Trainer Insurance - Example post','','publish','open','open','','personal-trainer-insurance-example-post','','','2016-07-31 14:53:00','2016-07-31 14:53:00','',0,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/?p=34',0,'post','',0),(37,2,'2016-07-31 14:51:20','2016-07-31 14:51:20','','Sport couple of athletes success','Successful couple of young athletes raising arms to golden summer sunset sky after training. Fitness man and woman with arms up celebrating sport goals after exercising in countryside field.','inherit','open','closed','','sport-couple-of-athletes-success','','','2016-07-31 14:51:20','2016-07-31 14:51:20','',34,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/iStock_27033536_SMALL.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(38,2,'2016-08-01 14:21:18','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Photographer Insurance','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2016-08-01 14:21:18','2016-08-01 14:21:18','',0,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/?page_id=38',0,'page','',0),(42,2,'2016-08-01 18:44:43','2016-08-01 18:44:43','','logo','','inherit','open','closed','','logo-2','','','2016-08-01 18:44:43','2016-08-01 18:44:43','',0,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/logo-1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(43,2,'2016-08-01 18:44:51','2016-08-01 18:44:51','','cropped-logo-1.png','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-logo-1-png','','','2016-08-01 18:44:51','2016-08-01 18:44:51','',0,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/cropped-logo-1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(52,2,'2016-08-04 10:33:52','2016-08-04 10:33:52','<strong>It all started with one simple question</strong>\r\n\r\nPhotography business was booming for Jesse Lake. A professional photographer for over ten years, he had helped hundreds of couples capture the most special day in their lives. He had earned a reputation among the locals and his photography business gained a lot of popularity. On this particular day, a female client by the name of Judith Praise walked into his office door accompanied by a muscular man with a mustache. Their wedding was around the corner and they needed a professional photographer for the day. She had been referred to Jesse by a friend and was optimistic his company was the perfect choice for her big day. After exchanging a few pleasantries, the routine consultation was underway. It all started with a simple question; which is the most suitable day for the video shoot? She also asked for professional advice on the best locations in town for photo-shoots and general advice on the day itself. Lake carefully noted the questions down and answered them to the best of his ability. He gave his professional advice to the best of his ability. This was his bread and butter and he did it with passion. He advised Judith and Marcel on a few good locations around town and suggested they take a reconnaissance tour of the spots before the wedding date. On the suitable day for the wedding video shooting, Jesse managed to convince Judith and Marcel to hold their wedding on Saturday. They agreed on the date, the total cost of the shooting and signed down the contract. After exchanging a few more extra words, Judith and Marcel were on their way. They left Jesse thinking about wedding and the preparations he needed to make. He was used to such scenarios and in the back of his mind he already envisioned a successful day at work come the wedding day. Little did he know that his decisions would come to haunt him later!\r\n\r\n<strong>The Perfect Day</strong>\r\n\r\nTwo weeks later, and Saturday was here! Jesse had made all the necessary preparations and he felt everything was on the right track. After assembling all the essentials for the photo-shoot, he, together with his two cameramen set out to the bride\'s house as agreed. The weather in the morning looked great and Jess was convinced that this was the perfect day for the shoot. As earlier recommended, Jess was supposed to start the video shoot at the bride’s home while two of his assistants worked in the groom’s home. The first few shots and videos in the morning were just perfect. The sun was all out and the mood was awesome. All over a sudden, it started looking cloudy and from a distance one could sense that torrential rains were coming. By the time the bridal party was getting to the photo-shoot spot that Jess had recommended, it was already drizzling and the clouds cast a gloomy shadow over the park making the video shoot so difficult. The park was not only muddy but had way too many trees which made it look so dark. Inside the cathedral, things were not any better. All the photos and videos looked really dark and the overall quality was so poor that the client ended up suing Luke. She claimed that the advice that Jess had given them greatly affected their decision to hold the wedding on Saturday. Judith claimed that he had misled her with faulty decisions and unprofessional advice. Right from the recommended date itself, suggested the photo-shoot locations to the quality of the videos produced everything seemed to work against Jess\r\n\r\n<strong>Without protection: where did Jess go wrong?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe legal suit filed against Jess and his business took a great toll on him and his business. He spent thousands of dollars hiring a lawyer to help him argue his case. He spent weeks in the courtroom and could not run his business during this time. He was still shocked that the client had sued him. Look, offering professional advice and recommendations was part of his business. He actually offered it as a bonus incentive and hardly charged a dime for the advice he gave out. All his previous clients had actually ended up tipping him handsomely after the advice he gave worked out great for them. He was still in shock that his free advice was threatening to bring his business down on its knees. A business he had toiled and moiled to set up for the last ten year. Six months in and out of the courtroom finally took their toll on Jesse’s photography business. He was ordered to pay a large sum of compensation fee to Judith and Marcel and ended up bankrupt. It’s at this point that he started regretting not having insured his photography business. He realized that without proper insurance, he was open to unwarranted suits by clients for even the smallest of reasons. Too bad, it was a little too late. Lack of insurance had seen him run bankrupt and lose his fortune.\r\n\r\n<strong>Professional Liability Insurance Could have saved Jesse and a thousand other photographers across the country</strong>\r\n\r\nSo, having have read the devastating story of Jesse and his downfall, what could he have done differently? Could a professional liability insurance saved our friend Jess’s business? The answer is yes. A professional liability insurance would have made all the difference. So why exactly is professional Liability Insurance important? Why should every photography business get this cover?\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Professional Liability Insurance Cover protects your photography business\r\nagainst errors and omissions, actual or alleged, which occur while providing your\r\nprofessional services. Let’s take our friend Jesse as an example, had he been under insurance coverage, he would not have been sued for giving inaccurate advice or recommendations. This means that you can freely advise your clients without the fear that your recommendations and suggestions would work against you.</li>\r\n 	<li>Liability cover protects you if you fail to deliver a service or delayed delivery of a service. Sometimes even after signing a contract with a client, it is not possible to turn up to deliver the service. Sometimes you are just a few minutes late. Without cover, you are at risk of being sued and paying compensation fines</li>\r\n 	<li>Professional Liability Insurance protects you against third party claims arising from services offered by your employers, temporarily hired assistants and independent contractors. This means that every member affiliated to your business is given cover when offering professional services for you or on your behalf.</li>\r\n 	<li>Accidents and injuries that arise when you are offering professional photography services area also covered. Damages to your protect or bodily injuries that arise from working in the field are duly taken care of.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nClearly, if you own a photography agency or run a photography business, Professional Liability Insurance Cover is an absolute necessity. Owing to the unpredictable nature of this business, you should not take chances. Always be protected. Be smart, don’t be like Jesse. Get a professional Liability Insurance Cover today!','The Cost of Advice: How Photographer Jesse Lake Went Bankrupt','','publish','open','open','','cost-advice-photographer-jesse-lake-went-bankrupt','','','2016-08-04 10:33:52','2016-08-04 10:33:52','',0,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/?p=52',0,'post','',0),(53,2,'2016-08-05 07:56:47','2016-08-05 07:56:47','<p>Your Name (required)<br />\n    [text* your-name] </p>\n\n<p>Your Email (required)<br />\n    [email* your-email] </p>\n\n<p>Subject<br />\n    [text your-subject] </p>\n\n<p>Your Message<br />\n    [textarea your-message] </p>\n\n<p>[submit \"Send\"]</p>\n \"[your-subject]\"\n[your-name] <wordpress@nextinsurance.wpengine.com>\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\nSubject: [your-subject]\n\nMessage Body:\n[your-message]\n\n--\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on  (http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com)\nevyatar@next-insurance.com\nReply-To: [your-email]\n\n0\n0\n\n \"[your-subject]\"\n <wordpress@nextinsurance.wpengine.com>\nMessage Body:\n[your-message]\n\n--\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on  (http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com)\n[your-email]\nReply-To: evyatar@next-insurance.com\n\n0\n0\nThank you for your message. It has been sent.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nOne or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nYou must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\nThe field is required.\nThe field is too long.\nThe field is too short.','Contact form 1','','publish','closed','closed','','contact-form-1','','','2016-08-05 07:56:47','2016-08-05 07:56:47','',0,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/?post_type=wpcf7_contact_form&p=53',0,'wpcf7_contact_form','',0),(54,2,'2016-08-05 10:53:24','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Elementor #54','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2016-08-05 10:53:24','2016-08-05 10:53:24','',0,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/?page_id=54',0,'page','',0),(56,2,'2016-08-07 14:21:48','2016-08-07 14:21:48','<strong>Free fall: keep your customers safe</strong>\r\n\r\nLucy was in her sixth year in photography. Her company; Lucillar Photography was doing so well that she had received a nomination for the annul photography awards nationwide. With ten employees and four studios across four cities, photography business had proven to be a very big success. On this day on a chilly Monday morning, she was opening the main office for the start of a busy week ahead. Political campaigns were around the corner and she was bracing herself for potential prominent political clients. Two hours into her Monday and one aspirant was on her door already. After the routine consultations and price agreement, they agreed that the photo-shoot for the main campaign posters would be conducted later that day in her main studio. Lucy was supposed to shoot the photos herself because she regarded the client as a VIP and only her was \'qualified’ enough for the shoot. She made the necessary preparations for a high end shoot and when the aspiring senator walked in with his entourage for the shoot, everything was ready. The first few shots were really great but Lucy still felt that the shoot had not captured the right angles and requested her client to switch positions on the high platform shooting seat. This is when all hell broke loose. The aspiring senator slipped from the seat, fell over and sprained his ankle. The guy who had otherwise been laid-back and very modest all along, started cursing and hurling nasty expletives at Lucy. He claimed that her substandard facilities; in this case her chair, had hugely contributed to his accident. He contacted his lawyer and three days later, a case was filed against Lucy and her company. She lost the case and had to not only pay for the medical expenses of the client but paid a fine of about $50K. Now that her business was not covered by an insurance, the suit and fine against her took a great toll on her business and she eventually had to close it down.Such a pity!\r\n\r\n<strong>Big data loss, huge financial risk</strong>\r\n\r\nSix days after meeting his client, Timothy Green was surprised to receive a call on a Saturday evening. He normally took weekends off to reminisce and spend time with his family and rarely received work related calls. Timothy Green a legendary photographer from St. Paul in Minnesota, had met with Fred Angers a week earlier after Fred had been referred to him by a friend. This was no surprise. Timothy had managed to win over the hearts of many using his camera lens. His photography skills coupled with charisma, had seen him become Minnesota’s favorite photographer. Referrals like Fred therefore were a common thing in his business. Fred Angers was a fashion stylist from Montpellier in France but was working with a local modelling company in Minneapolis. He wanted a skilled photographer with the expertise and dexterity to shoot photos of the models for an upcoming fashion magazine. As far as Minnesota was concerned at that time, such photographers didn’t come better than Timothy. They talked with Timothy and agreed on the time and locations for the shoots as well as the cost of the entire shoot. The shoot was scheduled for the coming Monday and therefore when Timothy received a call from Angers on Saturday, he was quite perplexed. Angers requested that they meet over coffee so that he could show Timothy a few photo examples and shooting ideas he had researched online. Timothy was a little skeptical at first but after a little convincing, he agreed to meet him later that evening in a local restaurant. They sipped the hot coffee while perusing through the photos and ideas that Angers had put together in his Mac laptop. Timothy was enjoying every moment of it and was amazed by the creativity of the tall skinny Frenchman. One particular shoot position impressed him and he wanted to take a closer look. As he attempted to pull the Mac laptop across the coffee table, all his hot coffee spilled on the laptop. In a minute or so, there was lengthy silence as Angers stared at him angrily with blazing eyes. The screen of the laptop cracked slightly but all the photo shoot images and some other significant data was lost in the process. Angers would not take any of it. He threatened to sue Tim if he didn’t replace the Mac book immediately. Without any insurance for his photography business, Timothy had to pay for the damage. He forked out a whopping $650000 because he didn’t want to be sued in court. The damages fee he paid crippled his business and he had to take a loan to revive the business again.\r\n\r\n<strong>One word too far: when personal insults destroy your business</strong>\r\n\r\nAfter taking photography classes for three straight years, Ken finally found a job with a small photography business in his town. It was during summer and there were very many clients visiting their offices to book their services for parties and weddings. Work was fine all along. He enjoyed working as an assistant photographer although he always felt he had the qualifications to be commanding the photography sessions himself. He was all over the place. Fresh from class, he was full of life and energy. He had lots of ideas and his boss was glad to have him around at all times. Ken had served three clients since morning and he was feeling rather elated. The day had been fine so far. The fourth client for the day was a young lady who was looking for a photography agency to hire for her birthday party. She was gorgeous and Ken didn’t hesitate to let her know. After exchanging a few pleasantries, they got down to business. Ken explained to her about the services and quoted her a price in between a few glances. To his bemusement, the lady wanted to hire their agency on credit. She was expecting some money at the end of the month and promised to pay once she had the cash. Laughing hysterically, Ken explained to her that they never offer their services on credit and that she would have to look for an alternative photography company for her upcoming party. Without much talk the lady went out of the office and walked towards the lift. Ken smiled at the thought of a gorgeous lady asking for their services on credit. It sounded so funny to him that he decided to share the story with the owner of a business located next to their office. He told Hassan about the gorgeous girl wanting their services on credit but exaggerated the story a little bit. He lied that the girl had asked for free services in return for sexual favors. All along as Ken and Hassan joked about the girl, they didn’t realize that she was in the next room consulting with another photography company. The rooms were close to each other and considering the way they were loudly talking and laughing, she had heard the whole story. She stormed back into Hassan’s room and started throwing tantrums while crying that Ken had offended her by spewing lies about her. Ken was so shocked that he could not utter a single word. He was forced to call his boss who was in town shopping for new cameras. He rushed back to the office and after listening to the story, he knew that his business was in deep trouble. The client then reported defamation to the police and sued the photography business for talking in an unflattering way about her. Without any insurance cover, the business had to pay a fine of $21000. A fee that brought the upcoming business down on its knees.\r\n\r\n<strong>General liability insurance would have protected all these;</strong>\r\n\r\nWe have seen three incidences of minor how minor mishaps in a normal business day in photography result into devastating losses and unwanted inconveniences. The reason all three of the above mentioned photography business ended up on the losing side, is because they lacked a general liability insurance cover for their businesses. Whether big business ( like in case #1 and case #2) or small upcoming photography business (like case #3) here is why you should always ensure that your business has a general liability insurance cover ;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>General liability insurance cover protects your business from lawsuits and claims in case of personal injuries inflicted to the client during the shoot. If a client or clients are injured on location, and you are insured, then the medical expenses will be covered by the insurance company. Amazing!</li>\r\n 	<li>General photographer liability insurance protects you and your business from cases of getting sued for damage of a client’s personal belonging on location. If a client\'\'s phone of property is damaged in your studio, you can rest assured that the insurance will cover you</li>\r\n 	<li>You can rest assured that there won’t be any nagging of lawsuits for damage caused by any of your permanent employees, temporary workers or anyone affiliated to your business. Photographer liability insurance covers them if only they were working for you at the time of the damage.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>It’s all worth it in the end;</strong>\r\n\r\nLook, some things that happen while working are out of our control. It is therefore important to take precautionary measures before we end up losing our businesses like our three friends did. No photographer whether a freelancer, enthusiast or even professional should even consider working without a general liability insurance cover for his/her business. It is all worth it in the end. For a reasonable sum a year, you can at least have the peace of mind knowing that help is right around the corner whenever incidences occur. Get a photographer liability insurance today, to evade a lot of unnecessary suing and potential loss to your photography business','3 Ridiculous Mistakes That Made Photographers Lose Their Business','','publish','open','open','','3-ridiculous-mistakes-made-photographers-lose-business','','','2016-08-07 14:21:48','2016-08-07 14:21:48','',0,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/?p=56',0,'post','',0),(58,2,'2016-08-15 14:31:18','2016-08-15 14:31:18','<strong>\"Most admired personal trainer in town”</strong>\r\n\r\nRon’s career as a personal trainer was nothing less of a fairy tale. Over the years, his excellent training skills and resources had helped establish a reputable business. Women trooped to his center in masses. As a matter of fact, from a point where he had to dish out flyers begging people to attend his gym, Ron had transitioned to a point where interested clients had to submit applications for consideration. In his hometown, Ron has helped many women to gain fitness and lose weight. Oblivious of the challenges that could face his business, Ron purely focused on making money and satisfying his ever growing customer base not realizing the importance a personal trainer insurance . To match his growing success, Ron laid plans that would see him not only expand his facility but also open new branches across his hometown and beyond. It always hurt him to have to turn away clients due to resource limitations and as such, he set out to save with an aim of opening more branches. Quite a vision, one would say. Little did Ron know that tragedy could strike at any time and hence saw no need to take a personal trainer insurance.\r\n\r\n<strong>That day at gym that Ron will never forget</strong>\r\n\r\nOn this fateful day, all started well for Ron. As usual. He woke up early morning to attend to his morning batch of clients. Things went quite well and the morning batch of clients left for work. Often, the morning batch was comprised of the working class client that had some experience in working out. However, the second batch attracted some novices as well. Well, as Ron was busy training this lot at the gym, tragedy struck. One of the new ladies that had just started training slipped and due to her inexperience, broke her leg. Conventionally, Ron should have been there to guide her but due to a large number of clients, he was busy with another client at the time. To Ron’s surprise, the broken leg would result in a 3-year period of disability. What followed was a chain of events that Ron had not anticipated. The lady threatened legal action forcing Ron to seek legal assistance. Surprisingly, the advocate he sought informed him that he was liable as this would count as negligence and as such, his only option was to negotiate with the lady for a settlement. After seeking the advice of several lawyers, Ron realized he had no other choice. How he wished that he had a personal trainer insurance.\r\n\r\n<strong> “I paid for the injury. And it was painful”</strong>\r\n\r\nEventually, Ron had to pay the lady for the injury. The price was enormous, Ron had to part with a whopping $82,000 wiping out not just his entire savings but also forcing him to seek a loan to cater for the deficit since her savings were not enough to cover everything. All his plans were shattered and rather than focus on expanding, Ron found himself having to focus on repaying the loan. This is when the reality struck Ron, had he had an insurance cover, he would not have had to pay, the insurance company would have paid. However, thanks to his ignorance, Ron found all his plan spoilt and his dream of opening new branches in the near future all shattered. What had seemed as an unnecessary expenditure, suddenly became an important necessity. As old adage would have it, “if wishes were horses, all beggars would ride”. Ron could only wish that he had insurance cover. Thinking back and imagining how many businesses suffer similar consequences, Ron could not hide his wish that all trainers should have an insurance policy to cater for foreseeable and unforeseeable circumstances. Eventually, with no funds and the resulting heavy debt, Ron had no choice but to wind a business he had worked too hard to build. In a blink, all that Ron had built over the years was over. His career as a personal trainer had met its tragic end. Ron case reflects millions of similar case that occur annually. With a professional liability insurance, Ron’s case would have been different.\r\n\r\n<strong>Professional liability insurance could save Ron’s career</strong>\r\n\r\nThe professional liability insurance or in this case, a personal trainer insurance, covers any financial obligations arising from errors, mistakes, oversights or any damages to individuals or property. With it, you can guarantee that any injury, damage, loss caused to any person or entity, either by you or any other persons acting on behalf of your business are fully covered. Professional liability insurance is based on turnover, workforce, and the activities practiced by the company.\r\n\r\nGuarantee for a local professional or a company should be a reflex when one becomes an entrepreneur. One should immediately think of the damage that may be caused. In addition, it is often mandatory in contracts for which a certificate of insurance is required when you install. But such assurances are not the only ones necessary for the proper functioning of a professional activity. As part of your professional activities, operation of your business, marketing your products or use of, or the services that you will make, you can cause damage to your employees, your customers or a third party. This is why professional liability insurance is essential. This is a blanket security. It allows you to secure the sustainability in light any major risks. Professional liability insurance is the best way to protect yourself against potential risks which could happen by you, that of your employees or that of your professional equipment.\r\n\r\nWithout proper insurance or in Ron’s case, personal trainer insurance, you may find yourself in a very difficult situation involving a civil offense. You will be ordered to pay you damages that may end up consuming your personal assets. In general, any professional activity is likely to cause damage. Under certain conditions, professional liability may be initiated and penalties imposed. The amounts involved sometimes exceed what people can pay by themselves. Civil liability is a legal obligation that requires anyone to repair damage to a victim occurring as a result of failure in his/her responsibility. If you have a professional liability insurance, the insurance will make such payments on your behalf.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','That one mistake that put an end to Ron’s career as a promising personal trainer','','publish','open','open','','one-mistake-put-end-rons-career-promising-personal-trainer','','','2016-08-15 14:31:18','2016-08-15 14:31:18','',0,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/?p=58',0,'post','',0),(59,2,'2016-08-15 14:51:04','2016-08-15 14:51:04','In this advent world today, no one is immune to a lawsuit. As with any profession where you have a client hire you for your expertise such as a personal trainer, you need to be prepared for accidents in case they happen. Personal trainer insurance is essential to protect oneself from any risks that may crop up when training clients in a private home studio or a gym and lead to a lawsuit.\r\n\r\n<strong>When a chill sunny day at park becomes a nightmare</strong>\r\n\r\nHere’s every personal trainer\'s nightmare: A lady files a lawsuit against her personal trainer claiming that she incurred an injury, got her knee broken from rigorous training sessions that left her in excruciating pain. The lady files a lawsuit against the trainer for bodily injury and is eligible for claiming compensation for her broken knee during a training session while using a TRX machine. This was due to the trainer’s negligence, carelessness and recklessness for setting up the TRX machine wrongly before exercise which resulted to the lady incurring a broken knee. In this case if the lady sues for bodily injury using the TRX machine as a result of negligence by the trainer due to: The trainer breached the duty of care and incurred a broken knee, failure to provide a personalized exercise routine as promised and failure to warn the plaintiff about the risks of injury associated with the TRX machine exercise. However, having a personal trainer’s liability can provide a trainer coverage and protection against such a claim. In this case, the trainer would have to suffer hefty charges and even have his license as a trainer revoked rendering him jobless. Due to the physical nature of the work a personal trainer does, the risk exists that a client can be harmed or can claim to be injured. In some cases, even when you guide physically healthy and fit people clients may have hidden physical health problems that may be aggravated by exercise. With insurance coverage, the trainer would be protected against this claim.\r\n\r\n<strong>The trainer who caused data loss</strong>\r\n\r\nAre you wondering how this could lead to a personal trainer lawsuit?\r\n\r\nDuring a training session, Tina a personal trainer from New York accidentally dropped a weight over her customer’s iPhone. The customer who was a businesswoman claimed that she had several important presentations that needed to be done and as a result, the data loss resulted in $42K damage. In this case, the customer sue\'s Tina for property damage and is eligible compensation for her iPhone and damages incurred by the loss of data. If Tina is not insured under General Liability insurance and the customer’s claim is successful, a court could award damages against Tina based on the seriousness of the data loss occurred resulting in very costly charges that may render Tina bankrupt. Thankfully General Limited insurance (explained further below) can prevent this. With General Liability, Tina’s policy would protect her from a lawsuit filed against her by the customer claiming that dropping the weights on her iPhone was her fault and she ought to have been more careful. Unfair don’t you think? But the court would not rule this case as unfair. Tina would be liable to pay a damage fee named by the court to cover the losses incurred from the data loss and have her replace the iPhone not to mention, the stress, pressure, and financial risks-money she would have to spend to cover the costs of the claims.\r\n\r\n<strong>The fat lady didn’t sing this time</strong>\r\n\r\nDo you think you could sue your personal trainer for saying mean things about you? Apparently, you can. In this case, James a personal trainer hired several employees to build training programs that fit his customers. One of the customers, Debbie, is an obese young woman who seeks training sessions to cut weight. While training, Debbie overhears David an employee of James talking in an unflattering way about her weight and gets very offended. Instead of letting it go, Debbie then decides to sue James for “Personal injury” due to David’s inconsiderate words that hurt her feelings claiming compensation. Here James (the personal trainer) is at risk of being held liable for this “Personal injury” even though he wasn’t the directly the one who hurt Debbie and would have to incur the damages ordered by court putting a financial risk on his business. Scary, huh!? I think so. With General liability Insurance coverage James can be covered against this claims hence not risk ruining his or the gym’s reputation or incurring huge financial risks in damages ordered by a court of law.\r\n\r\n<strong>So what is General Liability Coverage?</strong>\r\n\r\nSometimes referred to as commercial general Liability (CGL), General Liability Coverage is a personal trainer insurance that protects you and your business and covers the cost of your business from another person or business claims of body injury, associated medical costs and damage to property as a result of you supplying products or you going about your business. Business is intrinsically risky, but having a General Liability Coverage safeguards against many known and unknown risks. The General Liability coverage basically protects you and your business against third party claims. If you are a personal trainer (self-employed) and employ other staff in your business it is critical you consider investing in the General Liability Coverage. From the cases above, if each of the plaintiffs was insured under the General Liability Coverage they all would be safeguarded from all the claims stated against them, up to the limits of their policy. Policies under General Liability Coverage shield you as a personal trainer from litigation, an expense of out-of-court settlements and any judgments awarded by courts. No Fitness instructors and Personal trainers should consider taking the risks to operate a business without General Liability Coverage, it is definitely asking for trouble and putting oneself against huge financial risks to provide important liability protection to cover any unforeseeable risks against yourself and your business. Take your time, research and shop around to find the best policy on the General Liability Coverage that protects you and your business from any risks. For a reasonable sum of money a year, you can have a peace of mind knowing that help is right around the corner. Don’t get caught up in a nightmare lawsuit. As the old adage goes, it’s better to be safe than sorry (especially when your reputation is on the line)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Why those successful personal trainers lost their jobs?','','publish','open','open','','successful-personal-trainers-lost-jobs','','','2016-08-15 14:51:04','2016-08-15 14:51:04','',0,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/?p=59',0,'post','',0),(62,2,'2016-08-24 13:36:15','2016-08-24 13:36:15','Brad trained many of his clients in his house at Dayton in New Jersey most of his clients were people who were trying to control their BMI Body Mass index. The rise in life style diseases caused by high cholesterol intake immobility and lack of exercise such as obesity and Diabetes type II due to high BMI drove many people in the New Jersey to gyms. Those who could afford it like Carol, resorted to the services of a personal home trainer like Brad. Brad was ranked one of the best personal trainers in the Dayton area because he was result oriented. He pushed his clients to achieve visible results within a three month period. Carol went to Brad for training while she had a BMI of 35 and they had agreed that within the three months they would reduce her BMI to 27 which he assured Carol was possible. Carol was supposed to run a 3miles track in the morning then go for aerobics and weight training at his place in the evening every week day. Carol started the training and after working out for two weeks she complained to Brad that it was too much. Brad told Carol that if they were to reach their goal she had to continue with the exercises and introduced new equipment to hasten the results. After two more days of training Carol got a Knee ligament tear which she sued Brad for 300,000 USDs. Brad had to pay for this suit because the court considered this professional negligence.\r\n\r\nTraining clients at the gym had been Jessica job for the last 3years in Orlando Florida. She had almost perfected the art of aerobic exercise, resistant exercise and flexibility training. All the clients that enrolled in the gym she worked in were assigned a personal trainer. Jessica had successfully trained many clients in these three arts over the years and had seen clients fulfilled by the results they achieved in the gym. When Irene joined the gym Jessica was assigned as her personal trainer and as was normal they went through their exercise prescription and instruction, combined the three forms of training to achieve optimum results. One day as Jessica was training Irene she pushed her to do an over split because she thought that after six months of consistent training Irene was ready for the stretch. Jessica had done this with other clients and had successfully managed it. Irene got a muscle strain which rendered her immobile. Irene had to be rushed to the emergency room for her condition to be treated. Irene sued Jessica who had no professional indemnity cover; she was forced to pay even though the sum was hefty. The advice she gave to Irene was a professional mistake which she made, this made her sadly conclude that everybody makes mistakes but those without insurance had to pay for the damage.\r\n\r\nDiet is a vital part of any training regimen. Personal trainers are thoroughly trained on this aspect of personal training for total and wholesome fitness, Alex was no exception. She was trained on the different types of training which would ensure that her clients would get the results they were looking for when they engaged the services of a personal trainer. When Laurel enrolled in her gym she went over the types of physical training that they would undertake to tone her body and ensure that it would remain that way. Apart from the physical training Alex and Laurel went over Laurel diet plan. Laurel needed to slightly adjust her diet so as to shed a few pounds so that she could reach her ideal weight. Alex decided to remove some foods like cheese, butter and whole milk among others from her diet and introduce low fat milk and almonds which would ensure that she still got the nutritional benefits she required but consumed foods that were low in cholesterol and high in nutritious value. Laurel excitedly started on the diet the very next day. A few hours after taking her first serving of almonds she had to be hospitalized because she had an allergic reaction to the almonds which caused her to go into anaphylaxis which necessitated her being admitted to hospital. Even though Laurel wasn’t aware that she was allergic to almonds she sued Alex for professional negligence because a personal trainer is liable for the nutritional advice they give to their clients even when their clients go home.\r\n\r\nProfessional liability Insurance would have saved the above trainers a lot of money. PLI as it’s commonly or professional Indemnity Insurance is a form of liability insurance that guards a business against errors and omissions actual or alleged which occur while providing professional services. This includes incorrect advice given to a client, an omission or failing to deliver on a promised service. The coverage also protects from claims arising from services done by employees of a business, temporary staff and independent contractors. It is normally awarded in a civil lawsuit. The policy indemnifies a client to a professional service provider within a specific policy period. Claims made before the onset of cover are mainly not covered. Coverage does not include criminal prosecution or legal liability. Coverage is usually continued as long as the policy holder in this case the professional service provider, provides covered services or products plus the span of statutes of limitations: this means the policy gives a reasonable period in which claims can be lodged.\r\n\r\nBe it negligence, malpractice or errors or omissions, it is important that professionals service providers such as personal trainers and gym businesses obtain a professional liability Insurance policy which can save them lots of money in the long run in case of lawsuits by disgruntled clients. It is not easy to predict or remain assured that all the advice that a personal trainer will provide will be accurate and be suitable for all the clients that walk into their gym or business. Every advise works differently in every situation.','Those personal trainers lost their entire business and they have something to say','','publish','open','open','','personal-trainers-lost-entire-business-something-say','','','2016-08-24 13:36:15','2016-08-24 13:36:15','',0,'http://nextinsurance.wpengine.com/?p=62',0,'post','',0),(67,2,'2016-11-23 16:25:16','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2016-11-23 16:25:16','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://www.next-insurance.com/?p=67',0,'post','',0);
