,'2016-11-27 14:55:02','2016-11-27 14:55:02','<strong>“Most admired personal trainer in town”</strong>\r\n\r\nRon’s career as a personal trainer was nothing less of a fairy tale. Over the years, his excellent training skills and resources had helped establish a reputable business. Women trooped to his center in masses. As a matter of fact, from a point where he had to dish out flyers begging people to attend his gym, Ron had transitioned to a point where interested clients had to submit applications for consideration. In his hometown, Ron has helped many women to gain fitness and lose weight. Oblivious of the challenges that could face his business, Ron purely focused on making money and satisfying his ever growing customer base not realizing the importance a personal trainer insurance . To match his growing success, Ron laid plans that would see him not only expand his facility but also open new branches across his hometown and beyond. It always hurt him to have to turn away clients due to resource limitations and as such, he set out to save with an aim of opening more branches. Quite a vision, one would say. Little did Ron know that tragedy could strike at any time and hence saw no need to take a personal trainer insurance.\r\n\r\n<strong>That day at gym that Ron will never forget</strong>\r\n\r\nOn this fateful day, all started well for Ron. As usual. He woke up early morning to attend to his morning batch of clients. Things went quite well and the morning batch of clients left for work. Often, the morning batch was comprised of the working class client that had some experience in working out. However, the second batch attracted some novices as well. Well, as Ron was busy training this lot at the gym, tragedy struck. One of the new ladies that had just started training slipped and due to her inexperience, broke her leg. Conventionally, Ron should have been there to guide her but due to a large number of clients, he was busy with another client at the time. To Ron’s surprise, the broken leg would result in a 3-year period of disability. What followed was a chain of events that Ron had not anticipated. The lady threatened legal action forcing Ron to seek legal assistance. Surprisingly, the advocate he sought informed him that he was liable as this would count as negligence and as such, his only option was to negotiate with the lady for a settlement. After seeking the advice of several lawyers, Ron realized he had no other choice. How he wished that he had a personal trainer insurance.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-685\" src=\"http://www.next-insurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/iStock-478864354.jpg\" alt=\"Young sad woman injured her leg while male coach is helping her.\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1367\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>“I paid for the injury. And it was painful”</strong>\r\n\r\nEventually, Ron had to pay the lady for the injury. The price was enormous, Ron had to part with a whopping $82,000 wiping out not just his entire savings but also forcing him to seek a loan to cater for the deficit since her savings were not enough to cover everything. All his plans were shattered and rather than focus on expanding, Ron found himself having to focus on repaying the loan. This is when the reality struck Ron, had he had an insurance cover, he would not have had to pay, the insurance company would have paid. However, thanks to his ignorance, Ron found all his plan spoilt and his dream of opening new branches in the near future all shattered. What had seemed as an unnecessary expenditure, suddenly became an important necessity. As old adage would have it, “if wishes were horses, all beggars would ride”. Ron could only wish that he had insurance cover. Thinking back and imagining how many businesses suffer similar consequences, Ron could not hide his wish that all trainers should have an insurance policy to cater for foreseeable and unforeseeable circumstances. Eventually, with no funds and the resulting heavy debt, Ron had no choice but to wind a business he had worked too hard to build. In a blink, all that Ron had built over the years was over. His career as a personal trainer had met its tragic end. Ron case reflects millions of similar case that occur annually. With a professional liability insurance, Ron’s case would have been different.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Professional liability insurance could save Ron’s career</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-686 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"http://www.next-insurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/iStock-470950444-300x200.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\nThe professional liability insurance or in this case, a personal trainer insurance, covers any financial obligations arising from errors, mistakes, oversights or any damages to individuals or property. With it, you can guarantee that any injury, damage, loss caused to any person or entity, either by you or any other persons acting on behalf of your business are fully covered. Professional liability insurance is based on turnover, workforce, and the activities practiced by the company.\r\n\r\nGuarantee for a local professional or a company should be a reflex when one becomes an entrepreneur. One should immediately think of the damage that may be caused. In addition, it is often mandatory in contracts for which a certificate of insurance is required when you install. But such assurances are not the only ones necessary for the proper functioning of a professional activity. As part of your professional activities, operation of your business, marketing your products or use of, or the services that you will make, you can cause damage to your employees, your customers or a third party. This is why professional liability insurance is essential. This is a blanket security. It allows you to secure the sustainability in light any major risks. Professional liability insurance is the best way to protect yourself against potential risks which could happen by you, that of your employees or that of your professional equipment.\r\n\r\nWithout proper insurance or in Ron’s case, personal trainer insurance, you may find yourself in a very difficult situation involving a civil offense. You will be ordered to pay you damages that may end up consuming your personal assets. In general, any professional activity is likely to cause damage. Under certain conditions, professional liability may be initiated and penalties imposed. The amounts involved sometimes exceed what people can pay by themselves. Civil liability is a legal obligation that requires anyone to repair damage to a victim occurring as a result of failure in his/her responsibility. If you have a professional liability insurance, the insurance will make such payments on your behalf.','That one mistake that put an end to Ron’s career as a promising personal trainer','','draft','open','open','','one-mistake-put-end-rons-career-promising-personal-trainer','','','2016-12-07 23:49:05','2016-12-07 23:49:05','',0,'http://www.next-insurance.com/?p=683',0,'post','',0),(684,3,'2016-11-27 14:30:20','2016-11-27 14:30:20','','Personal Trainer Looking At People Doing Sit-Ups In Park','Young male fitness trainer looking at people doing sit-ups in park. Horizontal shot.','inherit','open','closed','','personal-trainer-looking-at-people-doing-sit-ups-in-park','','','2016-12-26 15:35:10','2016-12-26 15:35:10','',683,'http://www.next-insurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/iStock-476274054.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(685,3,'2016-11-27 14:33:48','2016-11-27 14:33:48','','Fitness instructor assisting young woman who had injured herself.','Young sad woman injured her leg while male coach is helping her.','inherit','open','closed','','fitness-instructor-assisting-young-woman-who-had-injured-herself','','','2016-12-26 15:35:05','2016-12-26 15:35:05','',683,'http://www.next-insurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/iStock-478864354.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(686,3,'2016-11-27 14:51:05','2016-11-27 14:51:05','','Protect your self concept on green blackboard','Protect your self concept on green blackboard','inherit','open','closed','','protect-your-self-concept-on-green-blackboard','','','2016-12-26 15:34:45','2016-12-26 15:34:45','',683,'http://www.next-insurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/iStock-470950444.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(688,3,'2016-11-27 15:20:04','2016-11-27 15:20:04','In this advent world today, no one is immune to a lawsuit. As with any profession where you have a client hire you for your expertise such as a personal trainer, you need to be prepared for accidents in case they happen. Personal trainer insurance is essential to protect oneself from any risks that may crop up when training clients in a private home studio or a gym and lead to a lawsuit.\r\n\r\n<strong>When a chill sunny day at park becomes a nightmare</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-690 alignleft\" src=\"http://www.next-insurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/iStock-467850843-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Young fitness man exercising with suspension trainer sling and personal sport trainer in City Park under summer trees\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\nHere’s every personal trainer\'s nightmare: A lady files a lawsuit against her personal trainer claiming that she incurred an injury, got her knee broken from rigorous training sessions that left her in excruciating pain. The lady files a lawsuit against the trainer for bodily injury and is eligible for claiming compensation for her broken knee during a training session while using a TRX machine. This was due to the trainer’s negligence, carelessness and recklessness for setting up the TRX machine wrongly before exercise which resulted to the lady incurring a broken knee. In this case if the lady sues for bodily injury using the TRX machine as a result of negligence by the trainer due to: The trainer breached the duty of care and incurred a broken knee, failure to provide a personalized exercise routine as promised and failure to warn the plaintiff about the risks of injury associated with the TRX machine exercise. However, having a personal trainer’s liability can provide a trainer coverage and protection against such a claim. In this case, the trainer would have to suffer hefty charges and even have his license as a trainer revoked rendering him jobless. Due to the physical nature of the work a personal trainer does, the risk exists that a client can be harmed or can claim to be injured. In some cases, even when you guide physically healthy and fit people clients may have hidden physical health problems that may be aggravated by exercise. With insurance coverage, the trainer would be protected against this claim.\r\n\r\n<strong>The trainer who caused data loss</strong>\r\n\r\nAre you wondering how this could lead to a personal trainer lawsuit?\r\n\r\nDuring a training session, Tina a personal trainer from New York accidentally dropped a weight over her customer’s iPhone. The customer who was a businesswoman claimed that she had several important presentations that needed to be done and as a result, the data loss resulted in $42K damage. In this case, the customer sue\'s Tina for property damage and is eligible compensation for her iPhone and damages incurred by the loss of data. If Tina is not insured under General Liability insurance and the customer’s claim is successful, a court could award damages against Tina based on the seriousness of the data loss occurred resulting in very costly charges that may render Tina bankrupt. Thankfully General Limited insurance (explained further below) can prevent this. With General Liability, Tina’s policy would protect her from a lawsuit filed against her by the customer claiming that dropping the weights on her iPhone was her fault and she ought to have been more careful. Unfair don’t you think? But the court would not rule this case as unfair. Tina would be liable to pay a damage fee named by the court to cover the losses incurred from the data loss and have her replace the iPhone not to mention, the stress, pressure, and financial risks-money she would have to spend to cover the costs of the claims.\r\n\r\n<strong>The fat lady didn’t sing this time</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-691 alignleft\" src=\"http://www.next-insurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/iStock-618608780-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Young sporty woman is discussing workout plan, progress and statistics with her fitness instructor using digital tablet.\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\nDo you think you could sue your personal trainer for saying mean things about you? Apparently, you can. In this case, James a personal trainer hired several employees to build training programs that fit his customers. One of the customers, Debbie, is an obese young woman who seeks training sessions to cut weight. While training, Debbie overhears David an employee of James talking in an unflattering way about her weight and gets very offended. Instead of letting it go, Debbie then decides to sue James for “Personal injury” due to David’s inconsiderate words that hurt her feelings claiming compensation. Here James (the personal trainer) is at risk of being held liable for this “Personal injury” even though he wasn’t the directly the one who hurt Debbie and would have to incur the damages ordered by court putting a financial risk on his business. Scary, huh!? I think so. With General liability Insurance coverage James can be covered against this claims hence not risk ruining his or the gym’s reputation or incurring huge financial risks in damages ordered by a court of law.\r\n\r\n<strong>So what is General Liability Coverage?</strong>\r\n\r\nSometimes referred to as commercial general Liability (CGL), General Liability Coverage is a personal trainer insurance that protects you and your business and covers the cost of your business from another person or business claims of body injury, associated medical costs and damage to property as a result of you supplying products or you going about your business. Business is intrinsically risky, but having a General Liability Coverage safeguards against many known and unknown risks. The General Liability coverage basically protects you and your business against third party claims. If you are a personal trainer (self-employed) and employ other staff in your business it is critical you consider investing in the General Liability Coverage. From the cases above, if each of the plaintiffs was insured under the General Liability Coverage they all would be safeguarded from all the claims stated against them, up to the limits of their policy. Policies under General Liability Coverage shield you as a personal trainer from litigation, an expense of out-of-court settlements and any judgments awarded by courts. No Fitness instructors and Personal trainers should consider taking the risks to operate a business without General Liability Coverage, it is definitely asking for trouble and putting oneself against huge financial risks to provide important liability protection to cover any unforeseeable risks against yourself and your business. Take your time, research and shop around to find the best policy on the General Liability Coverage that protects you and your business from any risks. For a reasonable sum of money a year, you can have a peace of mind knowing that help is right around the corner. Don’t get caught up in a nightmare lawsuit. As the old adage goes, it’s better to be safe than sorry (especially when your reputation is on the line).','Why those successful personal trainers lost their jobs?','','draft','open','open','','successful-personal-trainers-lost-jobs','','','2016-12-07 23:33:59','2016-12-07 23:33:59','',0,'http://www.next-insurance.com/?p=688',0,'post','',0),(689,3,'2016-11-27 15:08:41','2016-11-27 15:08:41','','Sporty woman doing push-ups under supervision of  personal trainer.','Young sporty w